  "texts": [
    "Another interpretation is that these RNA-binding IDRs are constitutively bound to RNA in cells where they exchange compaction-driving intramolecular protein-protein interactions for expansion-driving intermolecular protein-RNA interactions.",
    "Under this interpretation, compact IDRs are only compact",
    "https://doi.org/10.1038/s41592-023-02159-5",
    "in an unphysiological RNA-free context, such that they expand to envelop and chaperone RNA molecules, while themselves being reciprocally chaperoned by RNA.",
    "These interpretations are not mutually exclusive, nor do they prohibit a model in which RNA chaperoning requires many copies of RNA-binding proteins forming dynamic condensates."
  ],
